## v1.11.0 (2026-06-19)

Added phantom-recipe / stale-issue-description learnings from Odysseus Issue #182 (PR #312).

Previous version snapshot: v1.10.0 (2026-06-13)

Changes:

- **Learning — Issue describes multiple phantom recipes, only a subset are live defects** (from
  Odysseus #182): Issue claimed both `docs/onboarding.md:232` and `:233` had broken justfile
  recipe references. Ground-truth grep (`grep -E "^[a-z]" justfile`) showed line 232's recipe
  (`just start-agamemnon`) was already correct — only line 233 (`nestor-start` → `start-nestor`)
  was a live defect. The correct call: fix only the live defect, not the stale issue description.
  Added two new When-to-Use bullets (25–26), two new Failed-Attempts rows (issue line references
  and mixed naming convention), new Verified-On row, and a bulk cross-check snippet in
  Quick-Reference.
- **Learning — Justfiles can use mixed naming conventions** (from Odysseus #182): Odysseus uses
  verb-first (`start-agamemnon`, `start-nestor`) for Agamemnon/Nestor and prefix-first
  (`hermes-start`, `argus-start`, `keystone-start`) for infrastructure services. A doc with a mix
  of recipe references can have some correct and some phantom even in the same table section. Run
  a bulk cross-check of ALL table entries against the justfile, never assume consistency from
  seeing some entries correct.
- Updated `description:` field with trigger conditions 25–26 for the new learnings.
- Added four new tags: `phantom-recipe`, `justfile-ground-truth`, `stale-issue-description`,
  `mixed-naming-convention`.
- Bumped `version:` to `1.11.0`, updated `date:` to 2026-06-19.

## v1.10.0 (2026-06-13)

Salvaged six dropped learnings from closed PRs #2351/#2352/#2372/#2373/#2397/#2398/#2399/#2401
that were absorbed by carrier PR #2346 without their content being folded into the canonical skill.

Previous version snapshot: v1.9.0 (2026-06-13)

Changes:

- **Learning 1 — Count-annotates-curated-list rule** (from #2351/#2373): A doc count annotates
  its adjacent human-curated enumeration (tree, tier table, bullet list), not the raw filesystem.
  Bumping the number to `find … | wc -l` while the curated list is unchanged produces a
  contradictory doc (number > list_count) — a POLA NOGO worse than the original staleness.
  Correct fix: reconcile number-to-list (clarify scope/unit). Added §1a, verification one-liner,
  When-to-Use bullet, two new Failed-Attempts rows (bumped 19→20 without updating tree; trusted
  issue's stale 21-subpackage claim), and new Quick-Reference block.
- **Learning 2 — Verify replacement command actually runs before shipping** (from #2352): A
  feature name is not an environment name in pixi — `dev` may be in `[features]` not
  `[environments]`, making `pixi run -e dev` / `pixi shell -e dev` fail. Un-sourced commands
  are a STOP signal. Added §5c, pixi env verification command, When-to-Use bullet, new
  Failed-Attempts row, and Quick-Reference block.
- **Learning 3 — Pixi-only repos: prefix env tools with `pixi run`** (from #2372, verified-ci):
  Bare `pre-commit install`, `pytest`, `mypy`, `ruff` invocations fail on a clean machine
  (PATH does not include `.pixi/envs/default/bin`). Added §5b, detection grep, positive/negative
  verification pattern, When-to-Use bullet, new Failed-Attempts row, and Verified-On row.
- **Learning 4 — Enforced artifact > prose for conflicting counts** (from #2397): When an issue
  quotes two different numbers for the same thing, count from the passing test/enforced artifact
  (frozen-allowlist test, `expected_modules` set). Only add a prose guard when no enforced guard
  already exists. Added §6b, grep pattern for paraphrased counts, When-to-Use bullet, new
  Failed-Attempts row, and Verified-On row.
- **Learning 5 — Count-drift: re-derive from single source of truth with phrase-scoped grep**
  (from #2398): Re-derive from `pyproject.toml [project.scripts]` or equivalent manifest — never
  from a second doc. Phrase-scope the stale-number re-grep to scope the edit AND prove no copies
  survive. Prefer exact-string Edit over `replace_all` on bare digits. Added §6c, concrete example
  (37→47 tool count), When-to-Use bullet, new Failed-Attempts row, and Verified-On row.
- **Learning 6 — Content-anchored file:line citation repair + markdownlint-Skipped caveat**
  (from #2399/#2401): Locate dangling `file.py:NN` refs by content-match grep (not audit
  coordinate, which is off-by-one); replace with durable content-anchored citation; re-grep
  corpus post-fix; leave historical narrative intact. CAVEAT: `pre-commit run --files <doc>`
  prints `Skipped` when the hook's file filter excludes the path — the file was NOT linted.
  Added §3b, Quick-Reference block for file:line repair, markdownlint-Skipped caveat, When-to-Use
  bullet, two new Failed-Attempts rows, Key-parameters bullet, and Verified-On row.
- Updated `description:` field with trigger conditions 19–24 for the new learnings.
- Added six new tags: `count-annotates-list`, `pixi-environment`, `pixi-run-prefix`,
  `enforced-artifact`, `phrase-scoped-grep`, `file-line-citation`, `markdownlint-skipped`.
- Bumped `version:` to `1.10.0`, updated `date:` to 2026-06-13.

